      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "4a656bc480baeb7ca2745a9565742fbcaedd81c1",
            "subject": "LU-6120 lfsck: notify ever failed server to exit LFSCK"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Frank Zago",
          "email": "fzago@cray.com",
          "date": "2014-10-28 22:02:14.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-02-08 02:26:09.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5722 obdclass: reorganize busy object accounting",
        "message": "LU-5722 obdclass: reorganize busy object accounting\n\nDue to some accounting bug, lsb_busy of a hash bucket can become\nlarger than the total number of objects in said bucket. A busy object\ncan be counted more than once. When that happens, a negative value is\nreturned by the shrinker to Linux's shrink_slab() function. In older\nkernel, such as 2.6.32 used in RHEL 6, this will cause a forever loop\ninside shrink_slab(), in essence hanging the host.\n\nInstead of trying (and failing) to count the busy objects, count the\nobjects than are not busy, i.e. the objects that are present on the\nlsb_lru list. The number of busy objects is then the difference\nbetween the number of objects in the hash and the objects on the\nlsb_lru list.\n\nChange-Id: Ia6973991a1ff7fc53cdf8132bf2aab532934cf94\nSigned-off-by: frank zago <fzago@cray.com>\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/12468\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Mike Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
